        Syntactical Summary
            Pippen wakes from a nightmare and recollects the events leading to their capture
            The Urak-Hai is introduced as a ravenous group of orcs from many regions. Pippen secretly loosens his bonds.
            The orcs march west towards Isengard.
            The orcs untie the hobbits, and Pippen fakes an escape attempt to leave behind visible hobbit footprints.
            The orcs rea/ize they are being followed by white skins, and converse of their options
            The orcs continue on the road, getting in position to fight.
            Merry and Pippen observe the riders.
            Night arrives with a little unrest but no war.
            Pippen senses Grishnakh's desire for the ring, and baits him into bringing them away from the orcs.
            Merry and Pippen count there blessings and continue to run.
            The hobbits escape to the forest Fangorn as Eomer and his riders overtake and acheive victory over the orcs.
        Quotes
    Treebeard
    -- Pippen and Merry become acquainted with Treebeard and the Ents in Fangorn.
        Charcters
            Pippen
            Merry
            Fangorn (Treebeard)
            Finglos (Leaflock)
            Fladrif (Skinbark)
            Bregalad (Quickbeam)
        Places
            Fangorn
            Isengard
            Orchanc (The tower of Saruman in Isengard)
        Syntactical Summary
            Pippen and Merry wander in Fangorn a bit, and find a clearing in the trees
            The hobbits find the way to the clearing harder than they first thought.
            Treebeard reveals himself to the hobbits, and they become acquainted, the hobbits sharing their story of Gandalf and the orcs of Isengard to Treebeard.
            Treebeard tells a bit about Ents to the hobbits as he carries them to an Entish home.
            The group arrives at an Enthouse
            Treebeard shows them around and shares some water, in preparation to begin his tales.
            The hobbits recall their tale in detail, and then Treebeard talks of the Great War, of Saruman, and corses the betrayal of his dark union with the orcs.
            Treebeard begins to stage his uprising, before getting distracted telling the hobbits of the entwives
            Treebeard sings of the entwives
            They rest and wake to prepare for the "Entmoot", the gathering of the Ents.
            The entmoot begins, but the Hobbits become bored listening to the laborious entish language.
            The hobbits grow impatient, and treebeard assigns Bregalad (Quickbeam) to keep them company while the Ents finish the Moot. Quickbeams tells a bit of his story.
            The Ents finish their Moot, and begin their rally cries.
            A rally song
            Talk of the fight the Ents are preparing for.
            They begin their march to Isengard throught the forest.
        Quotes
            Often afterwards Pippen tried to describe his first impression of
            them. [Treebeards eyes]
            'One felt as if there was an enormous well behind them, filled up
            with ages of memory and long, slow, steady thinking; but their
            surface was sparkling with the the present; like sun shimmering on
            the outer leaves of a vast tree, or on the ripples of a very deep
            lake. I don't know, but it felt as if something that grew in the
            ground - asleep, you might say, or just feeling itself as
            something bettween root-tip and leaf-tip, between deep earth and
            sky had suddenly waked up, and was considering you with the same
            slow care that it had given to its own inside affairs for endless
            years.'
